## Key Architecture Decisions

- **Command → Agent → Skill**: all commands delegate to agents; agents consume skills
- **Hooks are deterministic gates**: security/quality rules live in hooks, NOT in CLAUDE.md
- **N1-N4b confidentiality**: every persisted file is classified before writing
- **150-line limit**: all files split at 150 lines — enforced by commit-guardian
- **SDD pipeline**: analyst → architect → spec-writer → developer → test-engineer → reviewer

## Project Structure

```
~/claude/
├── .claude/commands/ (506)    ← Slash command definitions (.md)
├── .claude/agents/ (47)       ← Subagent definitions (.md)
├── .claude/skills/ (88)       ← Reusable knowledge modules (SKILL.md)
├── .claude/hooks/ (35)        ← Deterministic lifecycle hooks (.sh)
├── .claude/rules/domain/ (136)← Domain rules loaded on demand
├── .claude/profiles/          ← User/company profiles (N3)
├── projects/ (gitignored)     ← Active client projects (N4)
├── output/ (gitignored)       ← Generated reports (N4)
└── scripts/                   ← Utility scripts
```

